# Debug API examples — requires DEBUG=true (docker-compose.debug.yml)
# VS Code: install "REST Client" extension and send requests from this file.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@initData = {{createInitData.response.body.init_data}}

### Health (debug)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/debug/health

### Generate test initData (use as X-Telegram-Init-Data header)
# @name createInitData
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/debug/init-data
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 123456789,
  "first_name": "Debug",
  "username": "debug_user"
}

### List packages
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/packages

### Checkout with Stars (needs valid BOT_TOKEN in .env)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/checkout
Content-Type: application/json
X-Telegram-Init-Data: {{initData}}

{
  "package_id": "starter",
  "method": "stars"
}

### List orders (debug)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/debug/orders

### Simulate payment for an order (replace ORDER_ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/debug/orders/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/simulate-payment
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### OpenAPI docs
# Browser: http://localhost:8000/docs
